 Review comment:
   While "Z" is a valid suffix to [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) timestamps, the name of the timezone wouldn't be "Z", it would be something like "UTC". 
   Besides, if the timezone is named e.g. "Europe/Paris", you don't want to append that to the formatted timestamp.

